		<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-68">
				<div id="div-comment-68" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn">Jason</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://cryptosource.org/bitcoin-mining-is-it-still-profitable/#comment-68">
			November 7, 2013 at 9:28 am</a>		</div>

		<p>I have done intensive investigations and right now you will lose money on most miners, the only people winning will be the people selling the miners.</p>
<p>This is based on a 20% increase every 2 weeks and at a price of $350 over the next year. Very few miners break even and a lot of people end of trying to cancel there orders.</p>
<p>Even if you reinvesting the bitcoins into mining it lags behind.</p>
<p>The best thing to do is just mine out with your current hardware then buy a new miner which will be far better for same price.</p>
<p>It&#8217;s very risky and 20% increases every 2 weeks from next year is a modest prediction, it could be as much as 30% which means only 3 miners currently make profits.</p>
<p>HashFast Sierra Batch 2 , HashFast Sierra Batch 2 and The Monarch from BFL, but this 3rd one hasn&#8217;t even shipped yet.</p>
<p>Adding delivery and time delays you can start going into negatives very quickly.</p>
<p>Its seems like buying bitcoins and holding onto them might be ur best bet.</p>

		<div class="reply">
			<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/bitcoin-mining-is-it-still-profitable/?replytocom=68#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("div-comment-68", "68", "respond", "1031")'>Reply</a>		</div>
